This paper is about a new neural network architecture for sequence transduction tasks, specifically machine translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the performance and efficiency of the model, which suggests it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions applying the model to English constituency parsing, which could also place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category.
